column5: Anybody know of any open source map packs available for an explorist 610? And is it worth it to buy them or will open source work? Thanks for any info.
you can load magic maps using vintage point. magic maps

I'm not sure about that GPS model, but I downloaded the Ibycus 4.0 Canada mapset and opened it up in a program on Linux (QLandKarte) and then exported all of Ontario in a format that works on my Garmin Dakota 20 handheld. You may be able to do the same for yours? The maps are quite good.
Hey Dana, got a way to do that for a Lowrance XOG?
no, it only works with garmin
I have a garmin for sale with all the maps.....
